cus Allen]] (1982\u20131992)\n*'''Receptions''': 1,070 [[Tim Brown (American football)|Tim Brown]] (1988\u20132003)\n*'''Receiving yards''': 14,734 [[Tim Brown (American football)|Tim Brown]] (1988\u20132003)\n*'''Receiving touchdowns''': 99 [[Tim Brown (American football)|Tim Brown]] (1988\u20132003)\n*'''Total touchdowns''': 104 [[Tim Brown (American football)|Tim Brown]] (1988\u20132003)\n*'''Points''': 1,799 [[Sebastian Janikowski]] (2000\u20132016)\n*'''Field goals made''': 414 [[Sebastian Janikowski]] (2000\u20132016)\n*'''Total punt yardage''': 48,215 [[Shane Lechler]] (2000\u20132012)\n*'''Punting average''': 47.5 [[Shane Lechler]] (2000\u20132012)\n*'''Kickoff return yards''': 4,841 [[Chris Carr (American football)|Chris Carr]] (2005\u20132007)\n*'''Punt Return yards''': 3,272 [[Tim Brown (American football)|Tim Brown]] (1988\u20132003)\n*'''Pass interceptions''': 39 [[Willie Brown (American football)|Willie Brown]] (1967\u20131978), [[Lester Hayes]] (1977\u20131986)\n*'''Defended passes/pass deflections''': 84 [[Charles Woodson]] (1998\u20132015)\n*'''Sacks''': 107.5 [[Greg Townsend]] (1983\u20131997)\n*'''Forced fumbles''': 18 [[Charles Woodson]] (1998\u20132015)\n*'''Winningest coach''': 103 [[John Madden]] (1969\u20131978)\n\n===Single-season leaders===\n*'''Passing yards''': 4,689 [[Rich Gannon]] (2002)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/teams/rai/single-season-passing.htm|title=Oakland/Los Angeles Raiders Single-Season Passing Leaders - Pro-Football-Reference.com|website=Pro-Football-Reference.com}}</ref>\n*'''Passing touchdowns''': 34 [[Daryle Lamonica]] (1969)\n*'''Rushing yards''': 1,759 [[Marcus Allen]] (1985)\n*'''Rushing touchdowns''': 16 [[Pete Banaszak]] (1975)\n*'''Receptions''': 104 [[Tim Brown (American football)|Tim Brown]] (1997)\n*'''Receiving yards''': 1,408 [[Tim Brown (American football)|Tim Brown]] (1997)\n*'''Receiving touchdowns''': 16 [[Art Powell (wide receiver)|Art Powell]] (1963)\n*'''Total touchdowns''':